377static int
378generic_codec_init_dacgroup(codec_t *this)
379{
380 int i, j, assoc, group;
381
382 /*
383 * grouping DACs
384 * [0] the lowest assoc DACs
385 * [1] the lowest assoc digital outputs
386 * [2] the 2nd assoc DACs
387 * :
388 */
389 this->dacs.ngroups = 0;
390 for (assoc = 0; assoc < CORB_CD_ASSOCIATION_MAX; assoc++) {
391 generic_codec_add_dacgroup(this, assoc, 0);
392 generic_codec_add_dacgroup(this, assoc, COP_AWCAP_DIGITAL);
393 }
394
395 /* find DACs which do not connect with any pins by default */
396 DPRINTF(("%s: find non-connected DACs\n", __func__));
397 FOR_EACH_WIDGET(this, i) {
398 bool found;
399
400 if (this->w[i].type != COP_AWTYPE_AUDIO_OUTPUT)
401 continue;
402 found = FALSE;
403 for (group = 0; group < this->dacs.ngroups; group++) {
404 for (j = 0; j < this->dacs.groups[group].nconv; j++) {
405 if (i == this->dacs.groups[group].conv[j]) {
406 found = TRUE;
407 group = this->dacs.ngroups;
408 break;
409 }
410 }
411 }
412 if (found)
413 continue;
414 if (this->dacs.ngroups >= 32)
415 break;
416 this->dacs.groups[this->dacs.ngroups].nconv = 1;
417 this->dacs.groups[this->dacs.ngroups].conv[0] = i;
418 this->dacs.ngroups++;
419 }
420 this->dacs.cur = 0;
421
422 /* enumerate ADCs */
423 this->adcs.ngroups = 0;
424 FOR_EACH_WIDGET(this, i) {
425 if (this->w[i].type != COP_AWTYPE_AUDIO_INPUT)
426 continue;
427 this->adcs.groups[this->adcs.ngroups].nconv = 1;
428 this->adcs.groups[this->adcs.ngroups].conv[0] = i;
429 this->adcs.ngroups++;
430 if (this->adcs.ngroups >= 32)
431 break;
432 }
433 this->adcs.cur = 0;
434 return 0;
435}
436
437static int
438generic_codec_add_dacgroup(codec_t *this, int assoc, uint32_t digital)
439{
440 int i, j, n, dac, seq;
441
442 n = 0;
443 for (seq = 0 ; seq < CORB_CD_SEQUENCE_MAX; seq++) {
444 i = generic_codec_find_pin(this, assoc, seq, digital);
445 if (i < 0)
446 continue;
447 dac = generic_codec_find_dac(this, i, 0);
448 if (dac < 0)
449 continue;
450 /* duplication check */
451 for (j = 0; j < n; j++) {
452 if (this->dacs.groups[this->dacs.ngroups].conv[j] == dac)
453 break;
454 }
455 if (j < n) /* this group already has <dac> */
456 continue;
457 this->dacs.groups[this->dacs.ngroups].conv[n++] = dac;
458 DPRINTF(("%s: assoc=%d seq=%d ==> g=%d n=%d\n",
459 __func__, assoc, seq, this->dacs.ngroups, n-1));
460 }
461 if (n <= 0) /* no such DACs */
462 return 0;
463 this->dacs.groups[this->dacs.ngroups].nconv = n;
464
465 /* check if the same combination is already registered */
466 for (i = 0; i < this->dacs.ngroups; i++) {
467 if (n != this->dacs.groups[i].nconv)
468 continue;
469 for (j = 0; j < n; j++) {
470 if (this->dacs.groups[this->dacs.ngroups].conv[j] !=
471 this->dacs.groups[i].conv[j])
472 break;
473 }
474 if (j >= n) /* matched */
475 return 0;
476 }
477 /* found no equivalent group */
478 this->dacs.ngroups++;
479 return 0;
480}
481
482static int
483generic_codec_find_pin(const codec_t *this, int assoc, int seq, uint32_t digital)
484{
485 int i;
486
487 FOR_EACH_WIDGET(this, i) {
488 if (this->w[i].type != COP_AWTYPE_PIN_COMPLEX)
489 continue;
490 if ((this->w[i].d.pin.cap & COP_PINCAP_OUTPUT) == 0)
491 continue;
492 if ((this->w[i].widgetcap & COP_AWCAP_DIGITAL) != digital)
493 continue;
494 if (this->w[i].d.pin.association != assoc)
495 continue;
496 if (this->w[i].d.pin.sequence == seq) {
497 return i;
498 }
499 }
500 return -1;
501}
502
503static int
504generic_codec_find_dac(const codec_t *this, int index, int depth)
505{
506 const widget_t *w;
507 int i, j, ret;
508
509 w = &this->w[index];
510 if (w->type == COP_AWTYPE_AUDIO_OUTPUT) {
511 DPRINTF(("%s: DAC: nid=0x%x index=%d\n",
512 __func__, w->nid, index));
513 return index;
514 }
515 if (++depth > 50) {
516 return -1;
517 }
518 if (w->selected >= 0) {
519 j = w->connections[w->selected];
520 if (VALID_WIDGET_NID(j, this)) {
521 ret = generic_codec_find_dac(this, j, depth);
522 if (ret >= 0) {
523 DPRINTF(("%s: DAC path: nid=0x%x index=%d\n",
524 __func__, w->nid, index));
525 return ret;
526 }
527 }
528 }
529 for (i = 0; i < w->nconnections; i++) {
530 j = w->connections[i];
531 if (!VALID_WIDGET_NID(j, this))
532 continue;
533 ret = generic_codec_find_dac(this, j, depth);
534 if (ret >= 0) {
535 DPRINTF(("%s: DAC path: nid=0x%x index=%d\n",
536 __func__, w->nid, index));
537 return ret;
538 }
539 }
540 return -1;
541}

543/* ----------------------------------------------------------------
544 * Generic mixer functions
545 * ---------------------------------------------------------------- */
546
547#define GMIDPRINTF(x) do {} while (0/*CONSTCOND*/)
548
549static int
550generic_mixer_init(codec_t *this)
551{
552 /*
553 * pin "<color>%2.2x"
554 * audio output "dac%2.2x"
555 * audio input "adc%2.2x"
556 * mixer "mixer%2.2x"
557 * selector "sel%2.2x"
558 */
559 mixer_item_t *m;
560 int err, i, j, k;
561
562 this->maxmixers = 10;
563 this->nmixers = 0;
564 this->szmixers = sizeof(mixer_item_t) * this->maxmixers;
565 this->mixers = kmem_zalloc(this->szmixers, KM_SLEEP);
566
567 /* register classes */
568 DPRINTF(("%s: register classes\n", __func__));
569 m = &this->mixers[AZ_CLASS_INPUT];
570 m->devinfo.index = AZ_CLASS_INPUT;
571 strlcpy(m->devinfo.label.name, AudioCinputs,
572 sizeof(m->devinfo.label.name));
573 m->devinfo.type = AUDIO_MIXER_CLASS;
574 m->devinfo.mixer_class = AZ_CLASS_INPUT;
575 m->devinfo.next = AUDIO_MIXER_LAST;
576 m->devinfo.prev = AUDIO_MIXER_LAST;
577 m->nid = 0;
578
579 m = &this->mixers[AZ_CLASS_OUTPUT];
580 m->devinfo.index = AZ_CLASS_OUTPUT;
581 strlcpy(m->devinfo.label.name, AudioCoutputs,
582 sizeof(m->devinfo.label.name));
583 m->devinfo.type = AUDIO_MIXER_CLASS;
584 m->devinfo.mixer_class = AZ_CLASS_OUTPUT;
585 m->devinfo.next = AUDIO_MIXER_LAST;
586 m->devinfo.prev = AUDIO_MIXER_LAST;
587 m->nid = 0;
588
589 m = &this->mixers[AZ_CLASS_RECORD];
590 m->devinfo.index = AZ_CLASS_RECORD;
591 strlcpy(m->devinfo.label.name, AudioCrecord,
592 sizeof(m->devinfo.label.name));
593 m->devinfo.type = AUDIO_MIXER_CLASS;
594 m->devinfo.mixer_class = AZ_CLASS_RECORD;
595 m->devinfo.next = AUDIO_MIXER_LAST;
596 m->devinfo.prev = AUDIO_MIXER_LAST;
597 m->nid = 0;
598
599 m = &this->mixers[AZ_CLASS_PLAYBACK];
600 m->devinfo.index = AZ_CLASS_PLAYBACK;
601 strlcpy(m->devinfo.label.name, AzaliaCplayback,
602 sizeof(m->devinfo.label.name));
603 m->devinfo.type = AUDIO_MIXER_CLASS;
604 m->devinfo.mixer_class = AZ_CLASS_PLAYBACK;
605 m->devinfo.next = AUDIO_MIXER_LAST;
606 m->devinfo.prev = AUDIO_MIXER_LAST;
607 m->nid = 0;
608
609 m = &this->mixers[AZ_CLASS_MIXER];
610 m->devinfo.index = AZ_CLASS_MIXER;
611 strlcpy(m->devinfo.label.name, AzaliaCmixer,
612 sizeof(m->devinfo.label.name));
613 m->devinfo.type = AUDIO_MIXER_CLASS;
614 m->devinfo.mixer_class = AZ_CLASS_MIXER;
615 m->devinfo.next = AUDIO_MIXER_LAST;
616 m->devinfo.prev = AUDIO_MIXER_LAST;
617 m->nid = 0;
618
619 this->nmixers = AZ_CLASS_MIXER + 1;
620
621#define MIXER_REG_PROLOG \
622 mixer_devinfo_t *d; \
623 err = generic_mixer_ensure_capacity(this, this->nmixers + 1); \
624 if (err) \
625 return err; \
626 m = &this->mixers[this->nmixers]; \
627 d = &m->devinfo; \
628 m->nid = i
629
630 FOR_EACH_WIDGET(this, i) {
631 const widget_t *w;
632
633 w = &this->w[i];
634
635 /* skip unconnected pins */
636 if (w->type == COP_AWTYPE_PIN_COMPLEX) {
637 uint8_t conn =
638 (w->d.pin.config & CORB_CD_PORT_MASK) >> 30;
639 if (conn == 1) /* no physical connection */
640 continue;
641 }
642
643 /* selector */
644 if (w->type != COP_AWTYPE_AUDIO_MIXER &&
645 w->type != COP_AWTYPE_POWER && w->nconnections >= 2) {
646 MIXER_REG_PROLOG;
647 GMIDPRINTF(("%s: selector %s\n", __func__, w->name));
648 snprintf(d->label.name, sizeof(d->label.name),
649 "%s.source", w->name);
650 d->type = AUDIO_MIXER_ENUM;
651 if (w->type == COP_AWTYPE_AUDIO_MIXER)
652 d->mixer_class = AZ_CLASS_RECORD;
653 else if (w->type == COP_AWTYPE_AUDIO_SELECTOR)
654 d->mixer_class = AZ_CLASS_INPUT;
655 else
656 d->mixer_class = AZ_CLASS_OUTPUT;
657 m->target = MI_TARGET_CONNLIST;
658 for (j = 0, k = 0; j < w->nconnections && k < 32; j++) {
659 uint8_t conn;
660
661 if (!VALID_WIDGET_NID(w->connections[j], this))
662 continue;
663 /* skip unconnected pins */
664 PIN_STATUS(&this->w[w->connections[j]],
665 conn);
666 if (conn == 1)
667 continue;
668 GMIDPRINTF(("%s: selector %d=%s\n", __func__, j,
669 this->w[w->connections[j]].name));
670 d->un.e.member[k].ord = j;
671 strlcpy(d->un.e.member[k].label.name,
672 this->w[w->connections[j]].name,
673 MAX_AUDIO_DEV_LEN);
674 k++;
675 }
676 d->un.e.num_mem = k;
677 this->nmixers++;
678 }
679
680 /* output mute */
681 if (w->widgetcap & COP_AWCAP_OUTAMP &&
682 w->outamp_cap & COP_AMPCAP_MUTE) {
683 MIXER_REG_PROLOG;
684 GMIDPRINTF(("%s: output mute %s\n", __func__, w->name));
685 snprintf(d->label.name, sizeof(d->label.name),
686 "%s.mute", w->name);
687 d->type = AUDIO_MIXER_ENUM;
688 if (w->type == COP_AWTYPE_AUDIO_MIXER)
689 d->mixer_class = AZ_CLASS_MIXER;
690 else if (w->type == COP_AWTYPE_AUDIO_SELECTOR)
691 d->mixer_class = AZ_CLASS_OUTPUT;
692 else if (w->type == COP_AWTYPE_PIN_COMPLEX)
693 d->mixer_class = AZ_CLASS_OUTPUT;
694 else
695 d->mixer_class = AZ_CLASS_INPUT;
696 m->target = MI_TARGET_OUTAMP;
697 d->un.e.num_mem = 2;
698 d->un.e.member[0].ord = 0;
699 strlcpy(d->un.e.member[0].label.name, AudioNoff,
700 MAX_AUDIO_DEV_LEN);
701 d->un.e.member[1].ord = 1;
702 strlcpy(d->un.e.member[1].label.name, AudioNon,
703 MAX_AUDIO_DEV_LEN);
704 this->nmixers++;
705 }
706
707 /* output gain */
708 if (w->widgetcap & COP_AWCAP_OUTAMP
709 && COP_AMPCAP_NUMSTEPS(w->outamp_cap)) {
710 MIXER_REG_PROLOG;
711 GMIDPRINTF(("%s: output gain %s\n", __func__, w->name));
712 snprintf(d->label.name, sizeof(d->label.name),
713 "%s", w->name);
714 d->type = AUDIO_MIXER_VALUE;
715 if (w->type == COP_AWTYPE_AUDIO_MIXER)
716 d->mixer_class = AZ_CLASS_MIXER;
717 else if (w->type == COP_AWTYPE_AUDIO_SELECTOR)
718 d->mixer_class = AZ_CLASS_OUTPUT;
719 else if (w->type == COP_AWTYPE_PIN_COMPLEX)
720 d->mixer_class = AZ_CLASS_OUTPUT;
721 else
722 d->mixer_class = AZ_CLASS_INPUT;
723 m->target = MI_TARGET_OUTAMP;
724 d->un.v.num_channels = WIDGET_CHANNELS(w);
725#ifdef MAX_VOLUME_255
726 d->un.v.units.name[0] = 0;
727#else
728 snprintf(d->un.v.units.name, sizeof(d->un.v.units.name),
729 "0.25x%ddB", COP_AMPCAP_STEPSIZE(w->outamp_cap)+1);
730#endif
731 d->un.v.delta =
732 MIXER_DELTA(COP_AMPCAP_NUMSTEPS(w->outamp_cap));
733 this->nmixers++;
734 }
735
736 /* input mute */
737 if (w->widgetcap & COP_AWCAP_INAMP &&
738 w->inamp_cap & COP_AMPCAP_MUTE) {
739 GMIDPRINTF(("%s: input mute %s\n", __func__, w->name));
740 if (w->type != COP_AWTYPE_AUDIO_SELECTOR &&
741 w->type != COP_AWTYPE_AUDIO_MIXER) {
742 MIXER_REG_PROLOG;
743 snprintf(d->label.name, sizeof(d->label.name),
744 "%s.mute", w->name);
745 d->type = AUDIO_MIXER_ENUM;
746 if (w->type == COP_AWTYPE_PIN_COMPLEX)
747 d->mixer_class = AZ_CLASS_OUTPUT;
748 else if (w->type == COP_AWTYPE_AUDIO_INPUT)
749 d->mixer_class = AZ_CLASS_RECORD;
750 else
751 d->mixer_class = AZ_CLASS_INPUT;
752 m->target = 0;
753 d->un.e.num_mem = 2;
754 d->un.e.member[0].ord = 0;
755 strlcpy(d->un.e.member[0].label.name,
756 AudioNoff, MAX_AUDIO_DEV_LEN);
757 d->un.e.member[1].ord = 1;
758 strlcpy(d->un.e.member[1].label.name,
759 AudioNon, MAX_AUDIO_DEV_LEN);
760 this->nmixers++;
761 } else {
762 uint8_t conn;
763
764 for (j = 0; j < w->nconnections; j++) {
765 MIXER_REG_PROLOG;
766 if (!VALID_WIDGET_NID(w->connections[j], this))
767 continue;
768
769 /* skip unconnected pins */
770 PIN_STATUS(&this->w[w->connections[j]],
771 conn);
772 if (conn == 1)
773 continue;
774
775 GMIDPRINTF(("%s: input mute %s.%s\n", __func__,
776 w->name, this->w[w->connections[j]].name));
777 generic_mixer_cat_names(
778 d->label.name,
779 sizeof(d->label.name),
780 w->name, this->w[w->connections[j]].name,
781 "mute");
782 d->type = AUDIO_MIXER_ENUM;
783 if (w->type == COP_AWTYPE_PIN_COMPLEX)
784 d->mixer_class = AZ_CLASS_OUTPUT;
785 else if (w->type == COP_AWTYPE_AUDIO_INPUT)
786 d->mixer_class = AZ_CLASS_RECORD;
787 else if (w->type == COP_AWTYPE_AUDIO_MIXER)
788 d->mixer_class = AZ_CLASS_MIXER;
789 else
790 d->mixer_class = AZ_CLASS_INPUT;
791 m->target = j;
792 d->un.e.num_mem = 2;
793 d->un.e.member[0].ord = 0;
794 strlcpy(d->un.e.member[0].label.name,
795 AudioNoff, MAX_AUDIO_DEV_LEN);
796 d->un.e.member[1].ord = 1;
797 strlcpy(d->un.e.member[1].label.name,
798 AudioNon, MAX_AUDIO_DEV_LEN);
799 this->nmixers++;
800 }
801 }
802 }
803
804 /* input gain */
805 if (w->widgetcap & COP_AWCAP_INAMP
806 && COP_AMPCAP_NUMSTEPS(w->inamp_cap)) {
807 GMIDPRINTF(("%s: input gain %s\n", __func__, w->name));
808 if (w->type != COP_AWTYPE_AUDIO_SELECTOR &&
809 w->type != COP_AWTYPE_AUDIO_MIXER) {
810 MIXER_REG_PROLOG;
811 snprintf(d->label.name, sizeof(d->label.name),
812 "%s", w->name);
813 d->type = AUDIO_MIXER_VALUE;
814 if (w->type == COP_AWTYPE_PIN_COMPLEX)
815 d->mixer_class = AZ_CLASS_OUTPUT;
816 else if (w->type == COP_AWTYPE_AUDIO_INPUT)
817 d->mixer_class = AZ_CLASS_RECORD;
818 else
819 d->mixer_class = AZ_CLASS_INPUT;
820 m->target = 0;
821 d->un.v.num_channels = WIDGET_CHANNELS(w);
822#ifdef MAX_VOLUME_255
823 d->un.v.units.name[0] = 0;
824#else
825 snprintf(d->un.v.units.name,
826 sizeof(d->un.v.units.name), "0.25x%ddB",
827 COP_AMPCAP_STEPSIZE(w->inamp_cap)+1);
828#endif
829 d->un.v.delta =
830 MIXER_DELTA(COP_AMPCAP_NUMSTEPS(w->inamp_cap));
831 this->nmixers++;
832 } else {
833 uint8_t conn;
834
835 for (j = 0; j < w->nconnections; j++) {
836 MIXER_REG_PROLOG;
837 if (!VALID_WIDGET_NID(w->connections[j], this))
838 continue;
839 /* skip unconnected pins */
840 PIN_STATUS(&this->w[w->connections[j]],
841 conn);
842 if (conn == 1)
843 continue;
844 GMIDPRINTF(("%s: input gain %s.%s\n", __func__,
845 w->name, this->w[w->connections[j]].name));
846 snprintf(d->label.name, sizeof(d->label.name),
847 "%s.%s", w->name,
848 this->w[w->connections[j]].name);
849 d->type = AUDIO_MIXER_VALUE;
850 if (w->type == COP_AWTYPE_PIN_COMPLEX)
851 d->mixer_class = AZ_CLASS_OUTPUT;
852 else if (w->type == COP_AWTYPE_AUDIO_INPUT)
853 d->mixer_class = AZ_CLASS_RECORD;
854 else if (w->type == COP_AWTYPE_AUDIO_MIXER)
855 d->mixer_class = AZ_CLASS_MIXER;
856 else
857 d->mixer_class = AZ_CLASS_INPUT;
858 m->target = j;
859 d->un.v.num_channels = WIDGET_CHANNELS(w);
860#ifdef MAX_VOLUME_255
861 d->un.v.units.name[0] = 0;
862#else
863 snprintf(d->un.v.units.name,
864 sizeof(d->un.v.units.name), "0.25x%ddB",
865 COP_AMPCAP_STEPSIZE(w->inamp_cap)+1);
866#endif
867 d->un.v.delta =
868 MIXER_DELTA(COP_AMPCAP_NUMSTEPS(w->inamp_cap));
869 this->nmixers++;
870 }
871 }
872 }
873
874 /* pin direction */
875 if (w->type == COP_AWTYPE_PIN_COMPLEX &&
876 w->d.pin.cap & COP_PINCAP_OUTPUT &&
877 w->d.pin.cap & COP_PINCAP_INPUT) {
878 MIXER_REG_PROLOG;
879 GMIDPRINTF(("%s: pin dir %s\n", __func__, w->name));
880 snprintf(d->label.name, sizeof(d->label.name),
881 "%s.dir", w->name);
882 d->type = AUDIO_MIXER_ENUM;
883 d->mixer_class = AZ_CLASS_OUTPUT;
884 m->target = MI_TARGET_PINDIR;
885 d->un.e.num_mem = 2;
886 d->un.e.member[0].ord = 0;
887 strlcpy(d->un.e.member[0].label.name, AudioNinput,
888 MAX_AUDIO_DEV_LEN);
889 d->un.e.member[1].ord = 1;
890 strlcpy(d->un.e.member[1].label.name, AudioNoutput,
891 MAX_AUDIO_DEV_LEN);
892 this->nmixers++;
893 }
894
895 /* pin headphone-boost */
896 if (w->type == COP_AWTYPE_PIN_COMPLEX &&
897 w->d.pin.cap & COP_PINCAP_HEADPHONE) {
898 MIXER_REG_PROLOG;
899 GMIDPRINTF(("%s: hpboost %s\n", __func__, w->name));
900 snprintf(d->label.name, sizeof(d->label.name),
901 "%s.boost", w->name);
902 d->type = AUDIO_MIXER_ENUM;
903 d->mixer_class = AZ_CLASS_OUTPUT;
904 m->target = MI_TARGET_PINBOOST;
905 d->un.e.num_mem = 2;
906 d->un.e.member[0].ord = 0;
907 strlcpy(d->un.e.member[0].label.name, AudioNoff,
908 MAX_AUDIO_DEV_LEN);
909 d->un.e.member[1].ord = 1;
910 strlcpy(d->un.e.member[1].label.name, AudioNon,
911 MAX_AUDIO_DEV_LEN);
912 this->nmixers++;
913 }
914
915 if (w->type == COP_AWTYPE_PIN_COMPLEX &&
916 w->d.pin.cap & COP_PINCAP_EAPD) {
917 MIXER_REG_PROLOG;
918 GMIDPRINTF(("%s: eapd %s\n", __func__, w->name));
919 snprintf(d->label.name, sizeof(d->label.name),
920 "%s.eapd", w->name);
921 d->type = AUDIO_MIXER_ENUM;
922 d->mixer_class = AZ_CLASS_OUTPUT;
923 m->target = MI_TARGET_EAPD;
924 d->un.e.num_mem = 2;
925 d->un.e.member[0].ord = 0;
926 strlcpy(d->un.e.member[0].label.name, AudioNoff,
927 MAX_AUDIO_DEV_LEN);
928 d->un.e.member[1].ord = 1;
929 strlcpy(d->un.e.member[1].label.name, AudioNon,
930 MAX_AUDIO_DEV_LEN);
931 this->nmixers++;
932 }
933
934 if (w->type == COP_AWTYPE_PIN_COMPLEX &&
935 w->d.pin.cap & COP_PINCAP_BALANCE) {
936 MIXER_REG_PROLOG;
937 GMIDPRINTF(("%s: balance %s\n", __func__, w->name));
938 snprintf(d->label.name, sizeof(d->label.name),
939 "%s.balance", w->name);
940 d->type = AUDIO_MIXER_ENUM;
941 if (w->type == COP_AWTYPE_PIN_COMPLEX)
942 d->mixer_class = AZ_CLASS_OUTPUT;
943 else if (w->type == COP_AWTYPE_AUDIO_INPUT)
944 d->mixer_class = AZ_CLASS_RECORD;
945 else
946 d->mixer_class = AZ_CLASS_INPUT;
947 m->target = MI_TARGET_BALANCE;
948 d->un.e.num_mem = 2;
949 d->un.e.member[0].ord = 0;
950 strlcpy(d->un.e.member[0].label.name, AudioNoff,
951 MAX_AUDIO_DEV_LEN);
952 d->un.e.member[1].ord = 1;
953 strlcpy(d->un.e.member[1].label.name, AudioNon,
954 MAX_AUDIO_DEV_LEN);
955 this->nmixers++;
956 }
957
958 if (w->widgetcap & COP_AWCAP_LRSWAP) {
959 MIXER_REG_PROLOG;
960 GMIDPRINTF(("%s: lrswap %s\n", __func__, w->name));
961 snprintf(d->label.name, sizeof(d->label.name),
962 "%s.lrswap", w->name);
963 d->type = AUDIO_MIXER_ENUM;
964 if (w->type == COP_AWTYPE_PIN_COMPLEX)
965 d->mixer_class = AZ_CLASS_OUTPUT;
966 else if (w->type == COP_AWTYPE_AUDIO_INPUT)
967 d->mixer_class = AZ_CLASS_RECORD;
968 else
969 d->mixer_class = AZ_CLASS_INPUT;
970 m->target = MI_TARGET_LRSWAP;
971 d->un.e.num_mem = 2;
972 d->un.e.member[0].ord = 0;
973 strlcpy(d->un.e.member[0].label.name, AudioNoff,
974 MAX_AUDIO_DEV_LEN);
975 d->un.e.member[1].ord = 1;
976 strlcpy(d->un.e.member[1].label.name, AudioNon,
977 MAX_AUDIO_DEV_LEN);
978 this->nmixers++;
979 }
980
981 /* volume knob */
982 if (w->type == COP_AWTYPE_VOLUME_KNOB &&
983 w->d.volume.cap & COP_VKCAP_DELTA) {
984 MIXER_REG_PROLOG;
985 GMIDPRINTF(("%s: volume knob %s\n", __func__, w->name));
986 strlcpy(d->label.name, w->name, sizeof(d->label.name));
987 d->type = AUDIO_MIXER_VALUE;
988 d->mixer_class = AZ_CLASS_OUTPUT;
989 m->target = MI_TARGET_VOLUME;
990 d->un.v.num_channels = 1;
991 d->un.v.units.name[0] = 0;
992 d->un.v.delta =
993 MIXER_DELTA(COP_VKCAP_NUMSTEPS(w->d.volume.cap));
994 this->nmixers++;
995 }
996 }
997
998 /* if the codec has multiple DAC groups, create "playback.mode" */
999 if (this->dacs.ngroups > 1) {
1000 MIXER_REG_PROLOG;
1001 GMIDPRINTF(("%s: create playback.mode\n", __func__));
1002 strlcpy(d->label.name, AudioNmode, sizeof(d->label.name));
1003 d->type = AUDIO_MIXER_ENUM;
1004 d->mixer_class = AZ_CLASS_PLAYBACK;
1005 m->target = MI_TARGET_DAC;
1006 for (i = 0; i < this->dacs.ngroups && i < 32; i++) {
1007 d->un.e.member[i].ord = i;
1008 for (j = 0; j < this->dacs.groups[i].nconv; j++) {
1009 if (j * 2 >= MAX_AUDIO_DEV_LEN)
1010 break;
1011 snprintf(d->un.e.member[i].label.name + j*2,
1012 MAX_AUDIO_DEV_LEN - j*2, "%2.2x",
1013 this->dacs.groups[i].conv[j]);
1014 }
1015 }
1016 d->un.e.num_mem = i;
1017 this->nmixers++;
1018 }
1019
1020 /* if the codec has multiple ADC groups, create "record.mode" */
1021 if (this->adcs.ngroups > 1) {
1022 MIXER_REG_PROLOG;
1023 GMIDPRINTF(("%s: create record.mode\n", __func__));
1024 strlcpy(d->label.name, AudioNmode, sizeof(d->label.name));
1025 d->type = AUDIO_MIXER_ENUM;
1026 d->mixer_class = AZ_CLASS_RECORD;
1027 m->target = MI_TARGET_ADC;
1028 for (i = 0; i < this->adcs.ngroups && i < 32; i++) {
1029 d->un.e.member[i].ord = i;
1030 for (j = 0; j < this->adcs.groups[i].nconv; j++) {
1031 if (j * 2 >= MAX_AUDIO_DEV_LEN)
1032 break;
1033 snprintf(d->un.e.member[i].label.name + j*2,
1034 MAX_AUDIO_DEV_LEN - j*2, "%2.2x",
1035 this->adcs.groups[i].conv[j]);
1036 }
1037 }
1038 d->un.e.num_mem = i;
1039 this->nmixers++;
1040 }
1041
1042 generic_mixer_fix_indexes(this);
1043 generic_mixer_default(this);
1044 return 0;
1045}
1046
1047static void
1048generic_mixer_cat_names(char *dst, size_t dstsize,
1049 const char *str1, const char *str2, const char *str3)
1050{
1051 const char *last2;
1052 size_t len1, len2, len3, total;
1053
1054 len1 = strlen(str1);
1055 len2 = strlen(str2);
1056 len3 = strlen(str3);
1057 total = len1 + 1 + len2 + 1 + len3 + 1;
1058 if (total - (len3 - 1) <= dstsize) {
1059 snprintf(dst, dstsize, "%s.%s.%s", str1, str2, str3);
1060 return;
1061 }
1062 last2 = len2 > 2 ? str2 + len2 - 2 : str2;
1063 if (len2 > 4) {
1064 snprintf(dst, dstsize, "%s.%.2s%s.%s", str1, str2, last2, str3);
1065 return;
1066 }
1067 snprintf(dst, dstsize, "%s.%s.%s", str1, last2, str3);
1068}
1069
1070static int
1071generic_mixer_ensure_capacity(codec_t *this, size_t newsize)
1072{
1073 size_t newmax;
1074 size_t newsz;
1075 void *newbuf;
1076
1077 if (this->maxmixers >= newsize)
1078 return 0;
1079 newmax = this->maxmixers + 10;
1080 if (newmax < newsize)
1081 newmax = newsize;
1082 newsz = sizeof(mixer_item_t) * newmax;
1083 newbuf = kmem_zalloc(newsz, KM_SLEEP);
1084 memcpy(newbuf, this->mixers, this->szmixers);
1085 kmem_free(this->mixers, this->szmixers);
1086 this->mixers = newbuf;
1087 this->szmixers = newsize;
1088 this->maxmixers = newmax;
1089 return 0;
1090}
1091
1092static int
1093generic_mixer_fix_indexes(codec_t *this)
1094{
1095 int i;
1096 mixer_devinfo_t *d;
1097
1098 for (i = 0; i < this->nmixers; i++) {
1099 d = &this->mixers[i].devinfo;
1100#ifdef DIAGNOSTIC
1101 if (d->index != 0 && d->index != i)
1102 aprint_error("%s: index mismatch %d %d\n", __func__,
1103 d->index, i);
1104#endif
1105 d->index = i;
1106 if (d->prev == 0)
1107 d->prev = AUDIO_MIXER_LAST;
1108 if (d->next == 0)
1109 d->next = AUDIO_MIXER_LAST;
1110 }
1111 return 0;
1112}
1113
1114static int
1115generic_mixer_default(codec_t *this)
1116{
1117 int i;
1118 mixer_item_t *m;
1119 /* unmute all */
1120 DPRINTF(("%s: unmute\n", __func__));
1121 for (i = 0; i < this->nmixers; i++) {
1122 mixer_ctrl_t mc;
1123
1124 m = &this->mixers[i];
1125 if (!IS_MI_TARGET_INAMP(m->target) &&
1126 m->target != MI_TARGET_OUTAMP)
1127 continue;
1128 if (m->devinfo.type != AUDIO_MIXER_ENUM)
1129 continue;
1130 mc.dev = i;
1131 mc.type = AUDIO_MIXER_ENUM;
1132 mc.un.ord = 0;
1133 generic_mixer_set(this, m->nid, m->target, &mc);
1134 }
1135
1136 /*
1137 * For bidirectional pins, make the default `output'
1138 */
1139 DPRINTF(("%s: process bidirectional pins\n", __func__));
1140 for (i = 0; i < this->nmixers; i++) {
1141 mixer_ctrl_t mc;
1142
1143 m = &this->mixers[i];
1144 if (m->target != MI_TARGET_PINDIR)
1145 continue;
1146 mc.dev = i;
1147 mc.type = AUDIO_MIXER_ENUM;
1148 mc.un.ord = 1; /* output */
1149 generic_mixer_set(this, m->nid, m->target, &mc);
1150 }
1151
1152 /* set unextreme volume */
1153 DPRINTF(("%s: set volume\n", __func__));
1154 for (i = 0; i < this->nmixers; i++) {
1155 mixer_ctrl_t mc;
1156
1157 m = &this->mixers[i];
1158 if (!IS_MI_TARGET_INAMP(m->target) &&
1159 m->target != MI_TARGET_OUTAMP &&
1160 m->target != MI_TARGET_VOLUME)
1161 continue;
1162 if (m->devinfo.type != AUDIO_MIXER_VALUE)
1163 continue;
1164 mc.dev = i;
1165 mc.type = AUDIO_MIXER_VALUE;
1166 mc.un.value.num_channels = 1;
1167 mc.un.value.level[0] = AUDIO_MAX_GAIN / 2;
1168 if (m->target != MI_TARGET_VOLUME &&
1169 WIDGET_CHANNELS(&this->w[m->nid]) == 2) {
1170 mc.un.value.num_channels = 2;
1171 mc.un.value.level[1] = AUDIO_MAX_GAIN / 2;
1172 }
1173 generic_mixer_set(this, m->nid, m->target, &mc);
1174 }
1175
1176 return 0;
1177}
1178
1179static int
1180generic_mixer_pin_sense(codec_t *this)
1181{
1182 typedef enum {
1183 PIN_DIR_IN,
1184 PIN_DIR_OUT,
1185 PIN_DIR_MIC
1186 } pintype_t;
1187 const widget_t *w;
1188 int i;
1189
1190 FOR_EACH_WIDGET(this, i) {
1191 pintype_t pintype = PIN_DIR_IN;
1192
1193 w = &this->w[i];
1194 if (w->type != COP_AWTYPE_PIN_COMPLEX)
1195 continue;
1196 if (!(w->d.pin.cap & COP_PINCAP_INPUT))
1197 pintype = PIN_DIR_OUT;
1198 if (!(w->d.pin.cap & COP_PINCAP_OUTPUT))
1199 pintype = PIN_DIR_IN;
1200
1201 switch (w->d.pin.device) {
1202 case CORB_CD_LINEOUT:
1203 case CORB_CD_SPEAKER:
1204 case CORB_CD_HEADPHONE:
1205 case CORB_CD_SPDIFOUT:
1206 case CORB_CD_DIGITALOUT:
1207 pintype = PIN_DIR_OUT;
1208 break;
1209 case CORB_CD_CD:
1210 case CORB_CD_LINEIN:
1211 pintype = PIN_DIR_IN;
1212 break;
1213 case CORB_CD_MICIN:
1214 pintype = PIN_DIR_MIC;
1215 break;
1216 }
1217
1218 switch (pintype) {
1219 case PIN_DIR_IN:
1220 this->comresp(this, w->nid,
1221 CORB_SET_PIN_WIDGET_CONTROL,
1222 CORB_PWC_INPUT, NULL);
1223 break;
1224 case PIN_DIR_OUT:
1225 this->comresp(this, w->nid,
1226 CORB_SET_PIN_WIDGET_CONTROL,
1227 CORB_PWC_OUTPUT, NULL);
1228 break;
1229 case PIN_DIR_MIC:
1230 this->comresp(this, w->nid,
1231 CORB_SET_PIN_WIDGET_CONTROL,
1232 CORB_PWC_INPUT|CORB_PWC_VREF_80, NULL);
1233 break;
1234 }
1235
1236 if (w->d.pin.cap & COP_PINCAP_EAPD) {
1237 uint32_t result;
1238 int err;
1239
1240 err = this->comresp(this, w->nid,
1241 CORB_GET_EAPD_BTL_ENABLE, 0, &result);
1242 if (err)
1243 continue;
1244 result &= 0xff;
1245 result |= CORB_EAPD_EAPD;
1246 err = this->comresp(this, w->nid,
1247 CORB_SET_EAPD_BTL_ENABLE, result, &result);
1248 if (err)
1249 continue;
1250 }
1251 }
1252
1253 return 0;
1254}
1255
1256static int
1257generic_mixer_widget_name(const codec_t *this, widget_t *w)
1258{
1259 const char *name = NULL, *grossloc = "", *geoloc = "";
1260 uint8_t grosslocval, geolocval;
1261
1262 if (w->type != COP_AWTYPE_PIN_COMPLEX)
1263 return 0;
1264
1265 switch (w->d.pin.device) {
1266 case CORB_CD_LINEOUT: name = "lineout"; break;
1267 case CORB_CD_SPEAKER: name = "spkr"; break;
1268 case CORB_CD_HEADPHONE: name = "hp"; break;
1269 case CORB_CD_CD: name = AudioNcd; break;
1270 case CORB_CD_SPDIFOUT: name = "spdifout"; break;
1271 case CORB_CD_DIGITALOUT: name = "digout"; break;
1272 case CORB_CD_MODEMLINE: name = "modemline"; break;
1273 case CORB_CD_MODEMHANDSET: name = "modemhset"; break;
1274 case CORB_CD_LINEIN: name = "linein"; break;
1275 case CORB_CD_AUX: name = AudioNaux; break;
1276 case CORB_CD_MICIN: name = AudioNmicrophone; break;
1277 case CORB_CD_TELEPHONY: name = "telephony"; break;
1278 case CORB_CD_SPDIFIN: name = "spdifin"; break;
1279 case CORB_CD_DIGITALIN: name = "digin"; break;
1280 case CORB_CD_DEVICE_OTHER: name = "reserved"; break;
1281 default: name = "unused"; break;
1282 }
1283
1284 grosslocval = ((w->d.pin.config & CORB_CD_LOCATION_MASK) >> 24) & 0xf;
1285 geolocval = (w->d.pin.config & CORB_CD_LOCATION_MASK) >> 28;
1286
1287 switch (geolocval) {
1288 case 0x00: /* external on primary chassis */
1289 case 0x10: /* external on separate chassis */
1290 geoloc = (geolocval == 0x00 ? "" : "d");
1291 switch (grosslocval) {
1292 case 0x00: grossloc = ""; break; /* N/A */
1293 case 0x01: grossloc = ""; break; /* rear */
1294 case 0x02: grossloc = ".front"; break; /* front */
1295 case 0x03: grossloc = ".left"; break; /* left */
1296 case 0x04: grossloc = ".right"; break; /* right */
1297 case 0x05: grossloc = ".top"; break; /* top */
1298 case 0x06: grossloc = ".bottom"; break; /* bottom */
1299 case 0x07: grossloc = ".rearpnl"; break; /* rear panel */
1300 case 0x08: grossloc = ".drivebay"; break; /* drive bay */
1301 default: grossloc = ""; break;
1302 }
1303 break;
1304 case 0x01:
1305 geoloc = "i";
1306 switch (grosslocval) {
1307 case 0x00: grossloc = ""; break; /* N/A */
1308 case 0x07: grossloc = ".riser"; break; /* riser */
1309 case 0x08: grossloc = ".hdmi"; break; /* hdmi */
1310 default: grossloc = ""; break;
1311 }
1312 break;
1313 default:
1314 geoloc = "o";
1315 switch (grosslocval) {
1316 case 0x00: grossloc = ""; break; /* N/A */
1317 case 0x06: grossloc = ".bottom"; break; /* bottom */
1318 case 0x07: grossloc = ".lidin"; break; /* lid inside */
1319 case 0x08: grossloc = ".lidout"; break; /* lid outside */
1320 default: grossloc = ""; break;
1321 }
1322 break;
1323 }
1324
1325 snprintf(w->name, sizeof(w->name), "%s%s%s", geoloc, name, grossloc);
1326 return 0;
1327}
1328
1329static int
1330generic_mixer_create_virtual(codec_t *this)
1331{
1332 mixer_item_t *m;
1333 mixer_devinfo_t *d;
1334 convgroup_t *cgdac = &this->dacs.groups[0];
1335 convgroup_t *cgadc = &this->adcs.groups[0];
1336 int i, err, mdac, madc, mmaster;
1337
1338 /* Clear mixer indexes, to make generic_mixer_fix_index happy */
1339 for (i = 0; i < this->nmixers; i++) {
1340 d = &this->mixers[i].devinfo;
1341 d->index = d->prev = d->next = 0;
1342 }
1343
1344 mdac = madc = mmaster = -1;
1345 for (i = 0; i < this->nmixers; i++) {
1346 if (this->mixers[i].devinfo.type != AUDIO_MIXER_VALUE)
1347 continue;
1348 if (mdac < 0 && this->dacs.ngroups > 0 && cgdac->nconv > 0) {
1349 if (this->mixers[i].nid == cgdac->conv[0])
1350 mdac = mmaster = i;
1351 }
1352 if (madc < 0 && this->adcs.ngroups > 0 && cgadc->nconv > 0) {
1353 if (this->mixers[i].nid == cgadc->conv[0])
1354 madc = i;
1355 }
1356 }
1357
1358 if (mdac == -1) {
1359 /*
1360 * no volume mixer found on the DAC; enumerate peer widgets
1361 * and try to find a volume mixer on them
1362 */
1363 widget_t *w;
1364 int j;
1365 FOR_EACH_WIDGET(this, i) {
1366 w = &this->w[i];
1367 for (j = 0; j < w->nconnections; j++)
1368 if (w->connections[j] == cgdac->conv[0])
1369 break;
1370
1371 if (j == w->nconnections)
1372 continue;
1373
1374 for (j = 0; j < this->nmixers; j++) {
1375 if (this->mixers[j].devinfo.type !=
1376 AUDIO_MIXER_VALUE)
1377 continue;
1378 if (this->mixers[j].nid == w->nid) {
1379 mdac = mmaster = j;
1380 break;
1381 }
1382 }
1383
1384 if (mdac == -1)
1385 break;
1386 }
1387 }
1388
1389 if (mdac >= 0) {
1390 err = generic_mixer_ensure_capacity(this, this->nmixers + 1);
1391 if (err)
1392 return err;
1393 m = &this->mixers[this->nmixers];
1394 d = &m->devinfo;
1395 memcpy(m, &this->mixers[mmaster], sizeof(*m));
1396 d->mixer_class = AZ_CLASS_OUTPUT;
1397 snprintf(d->label.name, sizeof(d->label.name), AudioNmaster);
1398 this->nmixers++;
1399
1400 err = generic_mixer_ensure_capacity(this, this->nmixers + 1);
1401 if (err)
1402 return err;
1403 m = &this->mixers[this->nmixers];
1404 d = &m->devinfo;
1405 memcpy(m, &this->mixers[mdac], sizeof(*m));
1406 d->mixer_class = AZ_CLASS_INPUT;
1407 snprintf(d->label.name, sizeof(d->label.name), AudioNdac);
1408 this->nmixers++;
1409 }
1410
1411 if (madc >= 0) {
1412 err = generic_mixer_ensure_capacity(this, this->nmixers + 1);
1413 if (err)
1414 return err;
1415 m = &this->mixers[this->nmixers];
1416 d = &m->devinfo;
1417 memcpy(m, &this->mixers[madc], sizeof(*m));
1418 d->mixer_class = AZ_CLASS_RECORD;
1419 snprintf(d->label.name, sizeof(d->label.name), AudioNvolume);
1420 this->nmixers++;
1421 }
1422
1423 generic_mixer_fix_indexes(this);
1424
1425 return 0;
1426}
1427
1428static int
1429generic_mixer_autoinit(codec_t *this)
1430{
1431 generic_mixer_init(this);
1432 generic_mixer_create_virtual(this);
1433 generic_mixer_pin_sense(this);
1434
1435 return 0;
1436}

1441 return generic_mixer_widget_name(this, w);

1453
1454/**
1455 * @param mc mc->type must be set by the caller before the call
1456 */
1457static int
1458generic_mixer_get(const codec_t *this, nid_t nid, int target, mixer_ctrl_t *mc)
1459{
1460 uint32_t result;
1461 nid_t n;
1462 int err;
1463
1464 /* inamp mute */
1465 if (IS_MI_TARGET_INAMP(target) && mc->type == AUDIO_MIXER_ENUM) {
1466 err = this->comresp(this, nid, CORB_GET_AMPLIFIER_GAIN_MUTE,
1467 CORB_GAGM_INPUT | CORB_GAGM_LEFT |
1468 MI_TARGET_INAMP(target), &result);
1469 if (err)
1470 return err;
1471 mc->un.ord = result & CORB_GAGM_MUTE ? 1 : 0;
1472 }
1473
1474 /* inamp gain */
1475 else if (IS_MI_TARGET_INAMP(target) && mc->type == AUDIO_MIXER_VALUE) {
1476 err = this->comresp(this, nid, CORB_GET_AMPLIFIER_GAIN_MUTE,
1477 CORB_GAGM_INPUT | CORB_GAGM_LEFT |
1478 MI_TARGET_INAMP(target), &result);
1479 if (err)
1480 return err;
1481 mc->un.value.level[0] = generic_mixer_from_device_value(this,
1482 nid, target, CORB_GAGM_GAIN(result));
1483 if (this->w[nid].type == COP_AWTYPE_AUDIO_SELECTOR ||
1484 this->w[nid].type == COP_AWTYPE_AUDIO_MIXER) {
1485 n = this->w[nid].connections[MI_TARGET_INAMP(target)];
1486#ifdef AZALIA_DEBUG
1487 if (!VALID_WIDGET_NID(n, this)) {
1488 DPRINTF(("%s: invalid target: nid=%d nconn=%d index=%d\n",
1489 __func__, nid, this->w[nid].nconnections,
1490 MI_TARGET_INAMP(target)));
1491 return EINVAL;
1492 }
1493#endif
1494 } else {
1495 n = nid;
1496 }
1497 mc->un.value.num_channels = WIDGET_CHANNELS(&this->w[n]);
1498 if (mc->un.value.num_channels == 2) {
1499 err = this->comresp(this, nid,
1500 CORB_GET_AMPLIFIER_GAIN_MUTE, CORB_GAGM_INPUT |
1501 CORB_GAGM_RIGHT | MI_TARGET_INAMP(target),
1502 &result);
1503 if (err)
1504 return err;
1505 mc->un.value.level[1] = generic_mixer_from_device_value
1506 (this, nid, target, CORB_GAGM_GAIN(result));
1507 }
1508 }
1509
1510 /* outamp mute */
1511 else if (target == MI_TARGET_OUTAMP && mc->type == AUDIO_MIXER_ENUM) {
1512 err = this->comresp(this, nid, CORB_GET_AMPLIFIER_GAIN_MUTE,
1513 CORB_GAGM_OUTPUT | CORB_GAGM_LEFT | 0, &result);
1514 if (err)
1515 return err;
1516 mc->un.ord = result & CORB_GAGM_MUTE ? 1 : 0;
1517 }
1518
1519 /* outamp gain */
1520 else if (target == MI_TARGET_OUTAMP && mc->type == AUDIO_MIXER_VALUE) {
1521 err = this->comresp(this, nid, CORB_GET_AMPLIFIER_GAIN_MUTE,
1522 CORB_GAGM_OUTPUT | CORB_GAGM_LEFT | 0, &result);
1523 if (err)
1524 return err;
1525 mc->un.value.level[0] = generic_mixer_from_device_value(this,
1526 nid, target, CORB_GAGM_GAIN(result));
1527 mc->un.value.num_channels = WIDGET_CHANNELS(&this->w[nid]);
1528 if (mc->un.value.num_channels == 2) {
1529 err = this->comresp(this, nid,
1530 CORB_GET_AMPLIFIER_GAIN_MUTE,
1531 CORB_GAGM_OUTPUT | CORB_GAGM_RIGHT | 0, &result);
1532 if (err)
1533 return err;
1534 mc->un.value.level[1] = generic_mixer_from_device_value
1535 (this, nid, target, CORB_GAGM_GAIN(result));
1536 }
1537 }
1538
1539 /* selection */
1540 else if (target == MI_TARGET_CONNLIST) {
1541 err = this->comresp(this, nid,
1542 CORB_GET_CONNECTION_SELECT_CONTROL, 0, &result);
1543 if (err)
1544 return err;
1545 result = CORB_CSC_INDEX(result);
1546 if (!VALID_WIDGET_NID(this->w[nid].connections[result], this))
1547 mc->un.ord = -1;
1548 else
1549 mc->un.ord = result;
1550 }
1551
1552 /* pin I/O */
1553 else if (target == MI_TARGET_PINDIR) {
1554 err = this->comresp(this, nid,
1555 CORB_GET_PIN_WIDGET_CONTROL, 0, &result);
1556 if (err)
1557 return err;
1558 mc->un.ord = result & CORB_PWC_OUTPUT ? 1 : 0;
1559 }
1560
1561 /* pin headphone-boost */
1562 else if (target == MI_TARGET_PINBOOST) {
1563 err = this->comresp(this, nid,
1564 CORB_GET_PIN_WIDGET_CONTROL, 0, &result);
1565 if (err)
1566 return err;
1567 mc->un.ord = result & CORB_PWC_HEADPHONE ? 1 : 0;
1568 }
1569
1570 /* DAC group selection */
1571 else if (target == MI_TARGET_DAC) {
1572 mc->un.ord = this->dacs.cur;
1573 }
1574
1575 /* ADC selection */
1576 else if (target == MI_TARGET_ADC) {
1577 mc->un.ord = this->adcs.cur;
1578 }
1579
1580 /* Volume knob */
1581 else if (target == MI_TARGET_VOLUME) {
1582 err = this->comresp(this, nid, CORB_GET_VOLUME_KNOB,
1583 0, &result);
1584 if (err)
1585 return err;
1586 mc->un.value.level[0] = generic_mixer_from_device_value(this,
1587 nid, target, CORB_VKNOB_VOLUME(result));
1588 mc->un.value.num_channels = 1;
1589 }
1590
1591 /* S/PDIF */
1592 else if (target == MI_TARGET_SPDIF) {
1593 err = this->comresp(this, nid, CORB_GET_DIGITAL_CONTROL,
1594 0, &result);
1595 if (err)
1596 return err;
1597 mc->un.mask = result & 0xff & ~(CORB_DCC_DIGEN | CORB_DCC_NAUDIO);
1598 } else if (target == MI_TARGET_SPDIF_CC) {
1599 err = this->comresp(this, nid, CORB_GET_DIGITAL_CONTROL,
1600 0, &result);
1601 if (err)
1602 return err;
1603 mc->un.value.num_channels = 1;
1604 mc->un.value.level[0] = CORB_DCC_CC(result);
1605 }
1606
1607 /* EAPD */
1608 else if (target == MI_TARGET_EAPD) {
1609 err = this->comresp(this, nid,
1610 CORB_GET_EAPD_BTL_ENABLE, 0, &result);
1611 if (err)
1612 return err;
1613 mc->un.ord = result & CORB_EAPD_EAPD ? 1 : 0;
1614 }
1615
1616 /* Balanced I/O */
1617 else if (target == MI_TARGET_BALANCE) {
1618 err = this->comresp(this, nid,
1619 CORB_GET_EAPD_BTL_ENABLE, 0, &result);
1620 if (err)
1621 return err;
1622 mc->un.ord = result & CORB_EAPD_BTL ? 1 : 0;
1623 }
1624
1625 /* LR-Swap */
1626 else if (target == MI_TARGET_LRSWAP) {
1627 err = this->comresp(this, nid,
1628 CORB_GET_EAPD_BTL_ENABLE, 0, &result);
1629 if (err)
1630 return err;
1631 mc->un.ord = result & CORB_EAPD_LRSWAP ? 1 : 0;
1632 }
1633
1634 else {
1635 aprint_error_dev(this->dev, "internal error in %s: target=%x\n",
1636 __func__, target);
1637 return -1;
1638 }
1639 return 0;
1640}
1641
1642static int
1643generic_mixer_set(codec_t *this, nid_t nid, int target, const mixer_ctrl_t *mc)
1644{
1645 uint32_t result, value;
1646 int err;
1647
1648 /* inamp mute */
1649 if (IS_MI_TARGET_INAMP(target) && mc->type == AUDIO_MIXER_ENUM) {
1650 /* We have to set stereo mute separately to keep each gain value. */
1651 err = this->comresp(this, nid, CORB_GET_AMPLIFIER_GAIN_MUTE,
1652 CORB_GAGM_INPUT | CORB_GAGM_LEFT |
1653 MI_TARGET_INAMP(target), &result);
1654 if (err)
1655 return err;
1656 value = CORB_AGM_INPUT | CORB_AGM_LEFT |
1657 (target << CORB_AGM_INDEX_SHIFT) |
1658 CORB_GAGM_GAIN(result);
1659 if (mc->un.ord)
1660 value |= CORB_AGM_MUTE;
1661 err = this->comresp(this, nid, CORB_SET_AMPLIFIER_GAIN_MUTE,
1662 value, &result);
1663 if (err)
1664 return err;
1665 if (WIDGET_CHANNELS(&this->w[nid]) == 2) {
1666 err = this->comresp(this, nid,
1667 CORB_GET_AMPLIFIER_GAIN_MUTE, CORB_GAGM_INPUT |
1668 CORB_GAGM_RIGHT | MI_TARGET_INAMP(target),
1669 &result);
1670 if (err)
1671 return err;
1672 value = CORB_AGM_INPUT | CORB_AGM_RIGHT |
1673 (target << CORB_AGM_INDEX_SHIFT) |
1674 CORB_GAGM_GAIN(result);
1675 if (mc->un.ord)
1676 value |= CORB_AGM_MUTE;
1677 err = this->comresp(this, nid,
1678 CORB_SET_AMPLIFIER_GAIN_MUTE, value, &result);
1679 if (err)
1680 return err;
1681 }
1682 }
1683
1684 /* inamp gain */
1685 else if (IS_MI_TARGET_INAMP(target) && mc->type == AUDIO_MIXER_VALUE) {
1686 if (mc->un.value.num_channels < 1)
1687 return EINVAL;
1688 if (!generic_mixer_validate_value(this, nid, target,
1689 mc->un.value.level[0]))
1690 return EINVAL;
1691 err = this->comresp(this, nid, CORB_GET_AMPLIFIER_GAIN_MUTE,
1692 CORB_GAGM_INPUT | CORB_GAGM_LEFT |
1693 MI_TARGET_INAMP(target), &result);
1694 if (err)
1695 return err;
1696 value = generic_mixer_to_device_value(this, nid, target,
1697 mc->un.value.level[0]);
1698 value = CORB_AGM_INPUT | CORB_AGM_LEFT |
1699 (target << CORB_AGM_INDEX_SHIFT) |
1700 (result & CORB_GAGM_MUTE ? CORB_AGM_MUTE : 0) |
1701 (value & CORB_AGM_GAIN_MASK);
1702 err = this->comresp(this, nid, CORB_SET_AMPLIFIER_GAIN_MUTE,
1703 value, &result);
1704 if (err)
1705 return err;
1706 if (mc->un.value.num_channels >= 2 &&
1707 WIDGET_CHANNELS(&this->w[nid]) == 2) {
1708 if (!generic_mixer_validate_value(this, nid, target,
1709 mc->un.value.level[1]))
1710 return EINVAL;
1711 err = this->comresp(this, nid,
1712 CORB_GET_AMPLIFIER_GAIN_MUTE, CORB_GAGM_INPUT |
1713 CORB_GAGM_RIGHT | MI_TARGET_INAMP(target),
1714 &result);
1715 if (err)
1716 return err;
1717 value = generic_mixer_to_device_value(this, nid, target,
1718 mc->un.value.level[1]);
1719 value = CORB_AGM_INPUT | CORB_AGM_RIGHT |
1720 (target << CORB_AGM_INDEX_SHIFT) |
1721 (result & CORB_GAGM_MUTE ? CORB_AGM_MUTE : 0) |
1722 (value & CORB_AGM_GAIN_MASK);
1723 err = this->comresp(this, nid,
1724 CORB_SET_AMPLIFIER_GAIN_MUTE, value, &result);
1725 if (err)
1726 return err;
1727 }
1728 }
1729
1730 /* outamp mute */
1731 else if (target == MI_TARGET_OUTAMP && mc->type == AUDIO_MIXER_ENUM) {
1732 err = this->comresp(this, nid, CORB_GET_AMPLIFIER_GAIN_MUTE,
1733 CORB_GAGM_OUTPUT | CORB_GAGM_LEFT, &result);
1734 if (err)
1735 return err;
1736 value = CORB_AGM_OUTPUT | CORB_AGM_LEFT | CORB_GAGM_GAIN(result);
1737 if (mc->un.ord)
1738 value |= CORB_AGM_MUTE;
1739 err = this->comresp(this, nid, CORB_SET_AMPLIFIER_GAIN_MUTE,
1740 value, &result);
1741 if (err)
1742 return err;
1743 if (WIDGET_CHANNELS(&this->w[nid]) == 2) {
1744 err = this->comresp(this, nid,
1745 CORB_GET_AMPLIFIER_GAIN_MUTE,
1746 CORB_GAGM_OUTPUT | CORB_GAGM_RIGHT, &result);
1747 if (err)
1748 return err;
1749 value = CORB_AGM_OUTPUT | CORB_AGM_RIGHT |
1750 CORB_GAGM_GAIN(result);
1751 if (mc->un.ord)
1752 value |= CORB_AGM_MUTE;
1753 err = this->comresp(this, nid,
1754 CORB_SET_AMPLIFIER_GAIN_MUTE, value, &result);
1755 if (err)
1756 return err;
1757 }
1758 }
1759
1760 /* outamp gain */
1761 else if (target == MI_TARGET_OUTAMP && mc->type == AUDIO_MIXER_VALUE) {
1762 if (mc->un.value.num_channels < 1)
1763 return EINVAL;
1764 if (!generic_mixer_validate_value(this, nid, target,
1765 mc->un.value.level[0]))
1766 return EINVAL;
1767 err = this->comresp(this, nid, CORB_GET_AMPLIFIER_GAIN_MUTE,
1768 CORB_GAGM_OUTPUT | CORB_GAGM_LEFT, &result);
1769 if (err)
1770 return err;
1771 value = generic_mixer_to_device_value(this, nid, target,
1772 mc->un.value.level[0]);
1773 value = CORB_AGM_OUTPUT | CORB_AGM_LEFT |
1774 (result & CORB_GAGM_MUTE ? CORB_AGM_MUTE : 0) |
1775 (value & CORB_AGM_GAIN_MASK);
1776 err = this->comresp(this, nid, CORB_SET_AMPLIFIER_GAIN_MUTE,
1777 value, &result);
1778 if (err)
1779 return err;
1780 if (mc->un.value.num_channels >= 2 &&
1781 WIDGET_CHANNELS(&this->w[nid]) == 2) {
1782 if (!generic_mixer_validate_value(this, nid, target,
1783 mc->un.value.level[1]))
1784 return EINVAL;
1785 err = this->comresp(this, nid,
1786 CORB_GET_AMPLIFIER_GAIN_MUTE, CORB_GAGM_OUTPUT |
1787 CORB_GAGM_RIGHT, &result);
1788 if (err)
1789 return err;
1790 value = generic_mixer_to_device_value(this, nid, target,
1791 mc->un.value.level[1]);
1792 value = CORB_AGM_OUTPUT | CORB_AGM_RIGHT |
1793 (result & CORB_GAGM_MUTE ? CORB_AGM_MUTE : 0) |
1794 (value & CORB_AGM_GAIN_MASK);
1795 err = this->comresp(this, nid,
1796 CORB_SET_AMPLIFIER_GAIN_MUTE, value, &result);
1797 if (err)
1798 return err;
1799 }
1800 }
1801
1802 /* selection */
1803 else if (target == MI_TARGET_CONNLIST) {
1804 if (mc->un.ord < 0 ||
1805 mc->un.ord >= this->w[nid].nconnections ||
1806 !VALID_WIDGET_NID(this->w[nid].connections[mc->un.ord], this))
1807 return EINVAL;
1808 err = this->comresp(this, nid,
1809 CORB_SET_CONNECTION_SELECT_CONTROL, mc->un.ord, &result);
1810 if (err)
1811 return err;
1812 }
1813
1814 /* pin I/O */
1815 else if (target == MI_TARGET_PINDIR) {
1816 if (mc->un.ord >= 2)
1817 return EINVAL;
1818 if (mc->un.ord == 0) {
1819 return generic_mixer_pinctrl(this, nid, CORB_PWC_INPUT);
1820 } else {
1821 return generic_mixer_pinctrl(
1822 this, nid, CORB_PWC_OUTPUT);
1823 }
1824 }
1825
1826 /* pin headphone-boost */
1827 else if (target == MI_TARGET_PINBOOST) {
1828 if (mc->un.ord >= 2)
1829 return EINVAL;
1830 err = this->comresp(this, nid,
1831 CORB_GET_PIN_WIDGET_CONTROL, 0, &result);
1832 if (err)
1833 return err;
1834 if (mc->un.ord == 0) {
1835 result &= ~CORB_PWC_HEADPHONE;
1836 } else {
1837 result |= CORB_PWC_HEADPHONE;
1838 }
1839 err = this->comresp(this, nid,
1840 CORB_SET_PIN_WIDGET_CONTROL, result, &result);
1841 if (err)
1842 return err;
1843 }
1844
1845 /* DAC group selection */
1846 else if (target == MI_TARGET_DAC) {
1847 if (this->running)
1848 return EBUSY;
1849 if (mc->un.ord >= this->dacs.ngroups)
1850 return EINVAL;
1851 return azalia_codec_construct_format(this,
1852 mc->un.ord, this->adcs.cur);
1853 }
1854
1855 /* ADC selection */
1856 else if (target == MI_TARGET_ADC) {
1857 if (this->running)
1858 return EBUSY;
1859 if (mc->un.ord >= this->adcs.ngroups)
1860 return EINVAL;
1861 return azalia_codec_construct_format(this,
1862 this->dacs.cur, mc->un.ord);
1863 }
1864
1865 /* Volume knob */
1866 else if (target == MI_TARGET_VOLUME) {
1867 if (mc->un.value.num_channels != 1)
1868 return EINVAL;
1869 if (!generic_mixer_validate_value(this, nid,
1870 target, mc->un.value.level[0]))
1871 return EINVAL;
1872 value = generic_mixer_to_device_value(this, nid, target,
1873 mc->un.value.level[0]) | CORB_VKNOB_DIRECT;
1874 err = this->comresp(this, nid, CORB_SET_VOLUME_KNOB,
1875 value, &result);
1876 if (err)
1877 return err;
1878 }
1879
1880 /* S/PDIF */
1881 else if (target == MI_TARGET_SPDIF) {
1882 err = this->comresp(this, nid, CORB_GET_DIGITAL_CONTROL,
1883 0, &result);
1884 result &= CORB_DCC_DIGEN | CORB_DCC_NAUDIO;
1885 result |= mc->un.mask & 0xff & ~CORB_DCC_DIGEN;
1886 err = this->comresp(this, nid, CORB_SET_DIGITAL_CONTROL_L,
1887 result, NULL);
1888 if (err)
1889 return err;
1890 } else if (target == MI_TARGET_SPDIF_CC) {
1891 if (mc->un.value.num_channels != 1)
1892 return EINVAL;
1893 if (mc->un.value.level[0] > 127)
1894 return EINVAL;
1895 err = this->comresp(this, nid, CORB_SET_DIGITAL_CONTROL_H,
1896 mc->un.value.level[0], NULL);
1897 if (err)
1898 return err;
1899 }
1900
1901 /* EAPD */
1902 else if (target == MI_TARGET_EAPD) {
1903 if (mc->un.ord >= 2)
1904 return EINVAL;
1905 err = this->comresp(this, nid,
1906 CORB_GET_EAPD_BTL_ENABLE, 0, &result);
1907 if (err)
1908 return err;
1909 result &= 0xff;
1910 if (mc->un.ord == 0) {
1911 result &= ~CORB_EAPD_EAPD;
1912 } else {
1913 result |= CORB_EAPD_EAPD;
1914 }
1915 err = this->comresp(this, nid,
1916 CORB_SET_EAPD_BTL_ENABLE, result, &result);
1917 if (err)
1918 return err;
1919 }
1920
1921 /* Balanced I/O */
1922 else if (target == MI_TARGET_BALANCE) {
1923 if (mc->un.ord >= 2)
1924 return EINVAL;
1925 err = this->comresp(this, nid,
1926 CORB_GET_EAPD_BTL_ENABLE, 0, &result);
1927 if (err)
1928 return err;
1929 result &= 0xff;
1930 if (mc->un.ord == 0) {
1931 result &= ~CORB_EAPD_BTL;
1932 } else {
1933 result |= CORB_EAPD_BTL;
1934 }
1935 err = this->comresp(this, nid,
1936 CORB_SET_EAPD_BTL_ENABLE, result, &result);
1937 if (err)
1938 return err;
1939 }
1940
1941 /* LR-Swap */
1942 else if (target == MI_TARGET_LRSWAP) {
1943 if (mc->un.ord >= 2)
1944 return EINVAL;
1945 err = this->comresp(this, nid,
1946 CORB_GET_EAPD_BTL_ENABLE, 0, &result);
1947 if (err)
1948 return err;
1949 result &= 0xff;
1950 if (mc->un.ord == 0) {
1951 result &= ~CORB_EAPD_LRSWAP;
1952 } else {
1953 result |= CORB_EAPD_LRSWAP;
1954 }
1955 err = this->comresp(this, nid,
1956 CORB_SET_EAPD_BTL_ENABLE, result, &result);
1957 if (err)
1958 return err;
1959 }
1960
1961 else {
1962 aprint_error_dev(this->dev, "internal error in %s: target=%x\n",
1963 __func__, target);
1964 return -1;
1965 }
1966 return 0;
1967}
1968
1969static int
1970generic_mixer_pinctrl(codec_t *this, nid_t nid, uint32_t value)
1971{
1972 int err;
1973 uint32_t result;
1974
1975 err = this->comresp(this, nid, CORB_GET_PIN_WIDGET_CONTROL, 0, &result);
1976 if (err)
1977 return err;
1978 result &= ~(CORB_PWC_OUTPUT | CORB_PWC_INPUT);
1979 result |= value & (CORB_PWC_OUTPUT | CORB_PWC_INPUT);
1980 return this->comresp(this, nid,
1981 CORB_SET_PIN_WIDGET_CONTROL, result, NULL);
1982}
1983
1984static u_char
1985generic_mixer_from_device_value(const codec_t *this, nid_t nid, int target,
1986 uint32_t dv)
1987{
1988#ifdef MAX_VOLUME_255
1989 uint32_t dmax;
1990
1991 if (IS_MI_TARGET_INAMP(target))
1992 dmax = COP_AMPCAP_NUMSTEPS(this->w[nid].inamp_cap);
1993 else if (target == MI_TARGET_OUTAMP)
1994 dmax = COP_AMPCAP_NUMSTEPS(this->w[nid].outamp_cap);
1995 else if (target == MI_TARGET_VOLUME)
1996 dmax = COP_VKCAP_NUMSTEPS(this->w[nid].d.volume.cap);
1997 else {
1998 printf("unknown target: %d\n", target);
1999 dmax = 127;
2000 }
2001 return dv * MIXER_DELTA(dmax);
2002#else
2003 return dv;
2004#endif
2005}
2006
2007static uint32_t
2008generic_mixer_to_device_value(const codec_t *this, nid_t nid, int target,
2009 u_char uv)
2010{
2011#ifdef MAX_VOLUME_255
2012 uint32_t dmax;
2013
2014 if (IS_MI_TARGET_INAMP(target))
2015 dmax = COP_AMPCAP_NUMSTEPS(this->w[nid].inamp_cap);
2016 else if (target == MI_TARGET_OUTAMP)
2017 dmax = COP_AMPCAP_NUMSTEPS(this->w[nid].outamp_cap);
2018 else if (target == MI_TARGET_VOLUME)
2019 dmax = COP_VKCAP_NUMSTEPS(this->w[nid].d.volume.cap);
2020 else {
2021 printf("unknown target: %d\n", target);
2022 dmax = 127;
2023 }
2024 return uv / MIXER_DELTA(dmax);
2025#else
2026 return uv;
2027#endif
2028}
2029
2030static uint32_t
2031generic_mixer_max(const codec_t *this, nid_t nid,
2032 int target)
2033{
2034#ifdef MAX_VOLUME_255
2035 return AUDIO_MAX_GAIN;
2036#else
2037 uint32_t dmax;
2038
2039 if (IS_MI_TARGET_INAMP(target))
2040 dmax = COP_AMPCAP_NUMSTEPS(this->w[nid].inamp_cap);
2041 else if (target == MI_TARGET_OUTAMP)
2042 dmax = COP_AMPCAP_NUMSTEPS(this->w[nid].outamp_cap);
2043 else if (target == MI_TARGET_VOLUME)
2044 dmax = COP_VKCAP_NUMSTEPS(this->w[nid].d.volume.cap);
2045 return dmax;
2046#endif
2047}
2048
2049static bool
2050generic_mixer_validate_value(const codec_t *this, nid_t nid,
2051 int target, u_char uv)
2052{
2053#ifdef MAX_VOLUME_255
2054 return TRUE;
2055#else
2056 return uv <= generic_mixer_max(this, nid, target);
2057#endif
2058}
2059
2060static int
2061generic_set_port(codec_t *this, mixer_ctrl_t *mc)
2062{
2063 const mixer_item_t *m;
2064
2065 if (mc->dev < 0 || mc->dev >= this->nmixers)
2066 return ENXIO;
2067 m = &this->mixers[mc->dev];
2068 if (mc->type != m->devinfo.type)
2069 return EINVAL;
2070 if (mc->type == AUDIO_MIXER_CLASS)
2071 return 0; /* nothing to do */
2072 return generic_mixer_set(this, m->nid, m->target, mc);
2073}
2074
2075static int
2076generic_get_port(codec_t *this, mixer_ctrl_t *mc)
2077{
2078 const mixer_item_t *m;
2079
2080 if (mc->dev < 0 || mc->dev >= this->nmixers)
2081 return ENXIO;
2082 m = &this->mixers[mc->dev];
2083 mc->type = m->devinfo.type;
2084 if (mc->type == AUDIO_MIXER_CLASS)
2085 return 0; /* nothing to do */
2086 return generic_mixer_get(this, m->nid, m->target, mc);
2087}

2232static int
2233alc260_mixer_init(codec_t *this)
2234{
2235 const mixer_item_t *mi;
2236 mixer_ctrl_t mc;
2237 uint32_t value;
2238
2239 switch (this->subid) {
2240 case ALC260_FUJITSU_ID:
2241 this->nmixers = __arraycount(alc260_loox_mixer_items);
2242 mi = alc260_loox_mixer_items;
2243 break;
2244 default:
2245 this->nmixers = __arraycount(alc260_mixer_items);
2246 mi = alc260_mixer_items;
2247 }
2248 this->szmixers = sizeof(mixer_item_t) * this->nmixers;
2249 this->mixers = kmem_alloc(this->szmixers, KM_SLEEP);
2250 memcpy(this->mixers, mi, sizeof(mixer_item_t) * this->nmixers);
2251 generic_mixer_fix_indexes(this);
2252 generic_mixer_default(this);
2253
2254 mc.dev = -1; /* no need for generic_mixer_set() */
2255 mc.type = AUDIO_MIXER_ENUM;
2256 mc.un.ord = 1; /* pindir: output */
2257 generic_mixer_set(this, 0x0f, MI_TARGET_PINDIR, &mc); /* lineout */
2258 generic_mixer_set(this, 0x10, MI_TARGET_PINDIR, &mc); /* headphones */
2259 mc.un.ord = 0; /* pindir: input */
2260 generic_mixer_set(this, 0x12, MI_TARGET_PINDIR, &mc); /* mic1 */
2261 generic_mixer_set(this, 0x13, MI_TARGET_PINDIR, &mc); /* mic2 */
2262 generic_mixer_set(this, 0x14, MI_TARGET_PINDIR, &mc); /* line1 */
2263 generic_mixer_set(this, 0x15, MI_TARGET_PINDIR, &mc); /* line2 */
2264 mc.un.ord = 0; /* mute: off */
2265 generic_mixer_set(this, 0x08, MI_TARGET_INAMP(0), &mc);
2266 generic_mixer_set(this, 0x08, MI_TARGET_INAMP(1), &mc);
2267 generic_mixer_set(this, 0x09, MI_TARGET_INAMP(0), &mc);
2268 generic_mixer_set(this, 0x09, MI_TARGET_INAMP(1), &mc);
2269 generic_mixer_set(this, 0x0a, MI_TARGET_INAMP(0), &mc);
2270 generic_mixer_set(this, 0x0a, MI_TARGET_INAMP(1), &mc);
2271 if (this->subid == ALC260_FUJITSU_ID) {
2272 mc.un.ord = 1; /* pindir: output */
2273 generic_mixer_set(this, 0x14, MI_TARGET_PINDIR, &mc); /* line1 */
2274 mc.un.ord = 4; /* connlist: cd */
2275 generic_mixer_set(this, 0x05, MI_TARGET_CONNLIST, &mc);
2276 /* setup a unsolicited event for the headphones */
2277 this->comresp(this, 0x14, CORB_SET_UNSOLICITED_RESPONSE,
2278 CORB_UNSOL_ENABLE | ALC260_EVENT_HP, NULL);
2279 this->extra[ALC260_EXTRA_MASTER] = 0; /* unmute */
2280 /* If the headphone presents, mute the internal speaker */
2281 this->comresp(this, 0x14, CORB_GET_PIN_SENSE, 0, &value);
2282 mc.un.ord = value & CORB_PS_PRESENCE ? 1 : 0;
2283 generic_mixer_set(this, 0x10, MI_TARGET_OUTAMP, &mc);
2284 this->get_port = alc260_get_port;
2285 }
2286 return 0;
2287}

2306
2307static int
2308alc260_set_port(codec_t *this, mixer_ctrl_t *mc)
2309{
2310 const mixer_item_t *m;
2311 mixer_ctrl_t mc2;
2312 uint32_t value;
2313 int err;
2314
2315 if (mc->dev < 0 || mc->dev >= this->nmixers)
2316 return ENXIO;
2317 m = &this->mixers[mc->dev];
2318 if (mc->type != m->devinfo.type)
2319 return EINVAL;
2320 if (mc->type == AUDIO_MIXER_CLASS)
2321 return 0;
2322 if (m->nid == 0x08 && m->target == MI_TARGET_OUTAMP) {
2323 DPRINTF(("%s: hook for outputs.master\n", __func__));
2324 err = generic_mixer_set(this, m->nid, m->target, mc);
2325 if (!err) {
2326 generic_mixer_set(this, 0x09, m->target, mc);
2327 mc2 = *mc;
2328 mc2.un.value.num_channels = 1;
2329 mc2.un.value.level[0] = (mc2.un.value.level[0]
2330 + mc2.un.value.level[1]) / 2;
2331 generic_mixer_set(this, 0x0a, m->target, &mc2);
2332 }
2333 return err;
2334 } else if (m->nid == 0x08 && m->target == MI_TARGET_INAMP(0)) {
2335 DPRINTF(("%s: hook for inputs.dac.mute\n", __func__));
2336 err = generic_mixer_set(this, m->nid, m->target, mc);
2337 if (!err) {
2338 generic_mixer_set(this, 0x09, m->target, mc);
2339 generic_mixer_set(this, 0x0a, m->target, mc);
2340 }
2341 return err;
2342 } else if (m->nid == 0x04 &&
2343 m->target == MI_TARGET_CONNLIST &&
2344 m->devinfo.un.e.num_mem == 2) {
2345 if (1 <= mc->un.ord && mc->un.ord <= 3)
2346 return EINVAL;
2347 } else if (m->nid == 0x05 &&
2348 m->target == MI_TARGET_CONNLIST &&
2349 m->devinfo.un.e.num_mem == 3) {
2350 if (1 <= mc->un.ord && mc->un.ord <= 3)
2351 return EINVAL;
2352 } else if (this->subid == ALC260_FUJITSU_ID && m->nid == 0x10 &&
2353 m->target == MI_TARGET_OUTAMP) {
2354 if (mc->un.ord != 0 && mc->un.ord != 1)
2355 return EINVAL;
2356 this->extra[ALC260_EXTRA_MASTER] = mc->un.ord;
2357 err = this->comresp(this, 0x14, CORB_GET_PIN_SENSE, 0, &value);
2358 if (err)
2359 return err;
2360 if (!(value & CORB_PS_PRESENCE)) {
2361 return generic_mixer_set(this, m->nid, m->target, mc);
2362 }
2363 return 0;
2364 }
2365 return generic_mixer_set(this, m->nid, m->target, mc);
2366}
2367
2368static int
2369alc260_get_port(codec_t *this, mixer_ctrl_t *mc)
2370{
2371 const mixer_item_t *m;
2372
2373 if (mc->dev < 0 || mc->dev >= this->nmixers)
2374 return ENXIO;
2375 m = &this->mixers[mc->dev];
2376 mc->type = m->devinfo.type;
2377 if (mc->type == AUDIO_MIXER_CLASS)
2378 return 0;
2379 if (this->subid == ALC260_FUJITSU_ID && m->nid == 0x10 &&
2380 m->target == MI_TARGET_OUTAMP) {
2381 mc->un.ord = this->extra[ALC260_EXTRA_MASTER];
2382 return 0;
2383 }
2384 return generic_mixer_get(this, m->nid, m->target, mc);
2385}
2386
2387static int
2388alc260_unsol_event(codec_t *this, int tag)
2389{
2390 int err;
2391 uint32_t value;
2392 mixer_ctrl_t mc;
2393
2394 switch (tag) {
2395 case ALC260_EVENT_HP:
2396 err = this->comresp(this, 0x14, CORB_GET_PIN_SENSE, 0, &value);
2397 if (err)
2398 break;
2399 mc.dev = -1;
2400 mc.type = AUDIO_MIXER_ENUM;
2401 if (value & CORB_PS_PRESENCE) {
2402 DPRINTF(("%s: headphone has been inserted.\n", __func__));
2403 mc.un.ord = 1; /* mute */
2404 generic_mixer_set(this, 0x10, MI_TARGET_OUTAMP, &mc);
2405 } else {
2406 DPRINTF(("%s: headphone has been pulled out.\n", __func__));
2407 mc.un.ord = this->extra[ALC260_EXTRA_MASTER];
2408 generic_mixer_set(this, 0x10, MI_TARGET_OUTAMP, &mc);
2409 }
2410 break;
2411 default:
2412 printf("%s: unknown tag: %d\n", __func__, tag);
2413 }
2414 return 0;
2415}

2813 generic_mixer_set(this, 0x1b, MI_TARGET_CONNLIST, &mc);
2814 mc.un.ord = 1; /* [1] 0x0d */

2865
2866static int
2867alc882_set_port(codec_t *this, mixer_ctrl_t *mc)
2868{
2869 const mixer_item_t *m;
2870 mixer_ctrl_t mc2;
2871 uint32_t mask, bit;
2872 int i, err;
2873
2874 if (mc->dev < 0 || mc->dev >= this->nmixers)
2875 return ENXIO;
2876 m = &this->mixers[mc->dev];
2877 if (mc->type != m->devinfo.type)
2878 return EINVAL;
2879 if (mc->type == AUDIO_MIXER_CLASS)
2880 return 0;
2881 if ((m->nid == 0x22 || m->nid == 0x23 || m->nid == 0x24)
2882 && m->target == -1) {
2883 DPRINTF(("%s: hook for record.*.source\n", __func__));
2884 mc2.dev = -1;
2885 mc2.type = AUDIO_MIXER_ENUM;
2886 bit = 1;
2887 mask = mc->un.mask & ALC882_MASK;
2888 for (i = 0; i < this->w[m->nid].nconnections && i < 32; i++) {
2889 mc2.un.ord = (mask & bit) ? 0 : 1;
2890 err = generic_mixer_set(this, m->nid,
2891 MI_TARGET_INAMP(i), &mc2);
2892 if (err)
2893 return err;
2894 bit = bit << 1;
2895 }
2896 return 0;
2897 }
2898 return generic_mixer_set(this, m->nid, m->target, mc);
2899}
2900
2901static int
2902alc882_get_port(codec_t *this, mixer_ctrl_t *mc)
2903{
2904 const mixer_item_t *m;
2905 uint32_t mask, bit, result;
2906 int i, err;
2907
2908 if (mc->dev < 0 || mc->dev >= this->nmixers)
2909 return ENXIO;
2910 m = &this->mixers[mc->dev];
2911 mc->type = m->devinfo.type;
2912 if (mc->type == AUDIO_MIXER_CLASS)
2913 return 0;
2914 if ((m->nid == 0x22 || m->nid == 0x23 || m->nid == 0x24)
2915 && m->target == -1) {
2916 DPRINTF(("%s: hook for record.*.source\n", __func__));
2917 mask = 0;
2918 bit = 1;
2919 for (i = 0; i < this->w[m->nid].nconnections && i < 32; i++) {
2920 err = this->comresp(this, m->nid, CORB_GET_AMPLIFIER_GAIN_MUTE,
2921 CORB_GAGM_INPUT | CORB_GAGM_LEFT |
2922 i, &result);
2923 if (err)
2924 return err;
2925 if ((result & CORB_GAGM_MUTE) == 0)
2926 mask |= bit;
2927 bit = bit << 1;
2928 }
2929 mc->un.mask = mask & ALC882_MASK;
2930 return 0;
2931 }
2932 return generic_mixer_get(this, m->nid, m->target, mc);
2933}

3152
3153static int
3154alc888_mixer_init(codec_t *this)
3155{
3156 mixer_item_t *m = NULL;
3157 mixer_devinfo_t *d;
3158 int err, i, mdac_index = -1;
3159
3160 err = generic_mixer_init(this);
3161 if (err)
3162 return err;
3163
3164 /* Clear mixer indexes, to make generic_mixer_fix_indexes happy */
3165 for (i = 0; i < this->nmixers; i++) {
3166 d = &this->mixers[i].devinfo;
3167 d->index = d->prev = d->next = 0;
3168 }
3169
3170 /* We're looking for front l/r mixer, which we know is nid 0x0c */
3171 for (i = 0; i < this->nmixers; i++)
3172 if (this->mixers[i].nid == 0x0c) {
3173 mdac_index = i;
3174 break;
3175 }
3176 if (mdac_index >= 0) {
3177 /*
3178 * ALC888 doesn't have a master mixer, so create a fake
3179 * inputs.dac that mirrors outputs.master
3180 */
3181 err = generic_mixer_ensure_capacity(this, this->nmixers + 1);
3182 if (err)
3183 return err;
3184
3185 m = &this->mixers[this->nmixers];
3186 d = &m->devinfo;
3187 memcpy(m, &this->mixers[mdac_index], sizeof(*m));
3188 d->mixer_class = AZ_CLASS_INPUT;
3189 snprintf(d->label.name, sizeof(d->label.name), AudioNdac);
3190 this->nmixers++;
3191 }
3192
3193 /* Recreate mixer indexes and defaults after making a mess of things */
3194 generic_mixer_fix_indexes(this);
3195 generic_mixer_default(this);
3196
3197 return 0;
3198}

3487static int
3488ad1983_mixer_init(codec_t *this)
3489{
3490 mixer_ctrl_t mc;
3491
3492 this->nmixers = __arraycount(ad1983_mixer_items);
3493 this->szmixers = sizeof(ad1983_mixer_items);
3494 this->mixers = kmem_alloc(this->szmixers, KM_SLEEP);
3495 memcpy(this->mixers, ad1983_mixer_items, sizeof(ad1983_mixer_items));
3496 generic_mixer_fix_indexes(this);
3497 generic_mixer_default(this);
3498
3499#define AD198X_EVENT_HP 1
3500#define AD198X_EVENT_SPEAKER 2
3501
3502 mc.dev = -1; /* no need for generic_mixer_set() */
3503 mc.type = AUDIO_MIXER_ENUM;
3504 mc.un.ord = 1; /* connlist: mixerout */
3505 generic_mixer_set(this, 0x05, MI_TARGET_CONNLIST, &mc);
3506 generic_mixer_set(this, 0x06, MI_TARGET_CONNLIST, &mc);
3507 mc.un.ord = 3; /* connlist: mixerout */
3508 generic_mixer_set(this, 0x0b, MI_TARGET_CONNLIST, &mc);
3509
3510 /* setup a unsolicited event for the headphones and speaker */
3511 this->comresp(this, 0x05, CORB_SET_UNSOLICITED_RESPONSE,
3512 CORB_UNSOL_ENABLE | AD198X_EVENT_SPEAKER, NULL);
3513 this->comresp(this, 0x06, CORB_SET_UNSOLICITED_RESPONSE,
3514 CORB_UNSOL_ENABLE | AD198X_EVENT_HP, NULL);
3515 ad1983_unsol_event(this, AD198X_EVENT_SPEAKER);
3516 ad1983_unsol_event(this, AD198X_EVENT_HP);
3517 return 0;
3518}
3519
3520static int
3521ad1983_unsol_event(codec_t *this, int tag)
3522{
3523 int err;
3524 uint32_t value;
3525 mixer_ctrl_t mc;
3526
3527 mc.dev = -1;
3528 mc.type = AUDIO_MIXER_ENUM;
3529
3530 switch (tag) {
3531 case AD198X_EVENT_HP:
3532 err = this->comresp(this, 0x06, CORB_GET_PIN_SENSE, 0, &value);
3533 if (err)
3534 break;
3535 if (value & CORB_PS_PRESENCE) {
3536 DPRINTF(("%s: headphone has been inserted.\n", __func__));
3537 mc.un.ord = 1; /* mute */
3538 generic_mixer_set(this, 0x05, MI_TARGET_OUTAMP, &mc);
3539 generic_mixer_set(this, 0x07, MI_TARGET_OUTAMP, &mc);
3540 } else {
3541 DPRINTF(("%s: headphone has been pulled out.\n", __func__));
3542 mc.un.ord = 0; /* unmute */
3543 generic_mixer_set(this, 0x05, MI_TARGET_OUTAMP, &mc);
3544 /* if no speaker unmute internal mono */
3545 err = this->comresp(this, 0x05, CORB_GET_PIN_SENSE, 0, &value);
3546 if (err)
3547 break;
3548 if (!(value & CORB_PS_PRESENCE))
3549 generic_mixer_set(this, 0x07, MI_TARGET_OUTAMP, &mc);
3550 }
3551 break;
3552 case AD198X_EVENT_SPEAKER:
3553 err = this->comresp(this, 0x05, CORB_GET_PIN_SENSE, 0, &value);
3554 if (err)
3555 break;
3556 if (value & CORB_PS_PRESENCE) {
3557 DPRINTF(("%s: speaker has been inserted.\n", __func__));
3558 mc.un.ord = 1; /* mute */
3559 generic_mixer_set(this, 0x07, MI_TARGET_OUTAMP, &mc);
3560 } else {
3561 DPRINTF(("%s: speaker has been pulled out.\n", __func__));
3562 /* if no headphones unmute internal mono */
3563 err = this->comresp(this, 0x06, CORB_GET_PIN_SENSE, 0, &value);
3564 if (err)
3565 break;
3566 if (!(value & CORB_PS_PRESENCE)) {
3567 mc.un.ord = 0; /* unmute */
3568 generic_mixer_set(this, 0x07, MI_TARGET_OUTAMP, &mc);
3569 }
3570 }
3571 break;
3572 default:
3573 printf("%s: unknown tag: %d\n", __func__, tag);
3574 }
3575 return 0;
3576}

4105static int
4106stac9221_gpio_unmute(codec_t *this, int pin)
4107{
4108 uint32_t data, mask, dir;
4109
4110 this->comresp(this, this->audiofunc, CORB_GET_GPIO_DATA, 0, &data);
4111 this->comresp(this, this->audiofunc,
4112 CORB_GET_GPIO_ENABLE_MASK, 0, &mask);
4113 this->comresp(this, this->audiofunc, CORB_GET_GPIO_DIRECTION, 0, &dir);
4114 data &= ~(1 << pin);
4115 mask |= 1 << pin;
4116 dir |= 1 << pin;
4117 this->comresp(this, this->audiofunc, 0x7e7, 0, NULL);
4118 this->comresp(this, this->audiofunc,
4119 CORB_SET_GPIO_ENABLE_MASK, mask, NULL);
4120 this->comresp(this, this->audiofunc,
4121 CORB_SET_GPIO_DIRECTION, dir, NULL);
4122 DELAY(1000);
4123 this->comresp(this, this->audiofunc, CORB_SET_GPIO_DATA, data, NULL);
4124 return 0;
4125}

4171static int
4172stac9200_mixer_init(codec_t *this)
4173{
4174 mixer_ctrl_t mc;
4175 uint32_t value;
4176
4177 this->nmixers = __arraycount(stac9200_mixer_items);
4178 this->szmixers = sizeof(stac9200_mixer_items);
4179 this->mixers = kmem_alloc(this->szmixers, KM_SLEEP);
4180 memcpy(this->mixers, stac9200_mixer_items, sizeof(stac9200_mixer_items));
4181 generic_mixer_fix_indexes(this);
4182 generic_mixer_default(this);
4183
4184 mc.dev = -1; /* no need for generic_mixer_set() */
4185 mc.type = AUDIO_MIXER_ENUM;
4186 mc.un.ord = 1; /* pindir: output */
4187 generic_mixer_set(this, 0x0d, MI_TARGET_PINDIR, &mc); /* headphones */
4188 generic_mixer_set(this, 0x0e, MI_TARGET_PINDIR, &mc); /* speaker */
4189 mc.un.ord = 0; /* pindir: input */
4190 generic_mixer_set(this, 0x0f, MI_TARGET_PINDIR, &mc); /* mic2 */
4191 generic_mixer_set(this, 0x10, MI_TARGET_PINDIR, &mc); /* mic1 */
4192 mc.type = AUDIO_MIXER_VALUE;
4193 mc.un.value.num_channels = 2;
4194 mc.un.value.level[0] = generic_mixer_max(this, 0x0c, MI_TARGET_OUTAMP);
4195 mc.un.value.level[1] = mc.un.value.level[0];
4196 generic_mixer_set(this, 0x0c, MI_TARGET_OUTAMP, &mc);
4197
4198#define STAC9200_DELL_INSPIRON6400_ID 0x01bd1028
4199#define STAC9200_DELL_INSPIRON9400_ID 0x01cd1028
4200#define STAC9200_DELL_640M_ID 0x01d81028
4201#define STAC9200_DELL_LATITUDE_D420_ID 0x01d61028
4202#define STAC9200_DELL_LATITUDE_D430_ID 0x02011028
4203
4204#define STAC9200_EVENT_HP 0
4205#define STAC9200_NID_HP 0x0d
4206#define STAC9200_NID_SPEAKER 0x0e
4207
4208 switch (this->subid) {
4209 case STAC9200_DELL_INSPIRON6400_ID:
4210 case STAC9200_DELL_INSPIRON9400_ID:
4211 case STAC9200_DELL_640M_ID:
4212 case STAC9200_DELL_LATITUDE_D420_ID:
4213 case STAC9200_DELL_LATITUDE_D430_ID:
4214 /* Does every DELL model have the same pin configuration?
4215 * I'm not sure. */
4216
4217 /* setup a unsolicited event for the headphones */
4218 this->comresp(this, STAC9200_NID_HP, CORB_SET_UNSOLICITED_RESPONSE,
4219 CORB_UNSOL_ENABLE | STAC9200_EVENT_HP, NULL);
4220 /* If the headphone presents, mute the internal speaker */
4221 this->comresp(this, STAC9200_NID_HP, CORB_GET_PIN_SENSE, 0, &value);
4222 if (value & CORB_PS_PRESENCE) {
4223 generic_mixer_pinctrl(this, STAC9200_NID_SPEAKER, 0);
4224 } else {
4225 generic_mixer_pinctrl(this,
4226 STAC9200_NID_SPEAKER, CORB_PWC_OUTPUT);
4227 }
4228 break;
4229 default:
4230 break;
4231 }
4232 return 0;
4233}
4234
4235static int
4236stac9200_unsol_event(codec_t *this, int tag)
4237{
4238 int err;
4239 uint32_t value;
4240
4241 switch (tag) {
4242 case STAC9200_EVENT_HP:
4243 err = this->comresp(this, STAC9200_NID_HP,
4244 CORB_GET_PIN_SENSE, 0, &value);
4245 if (err)
4246 break;
4247 if (value & CORB_PS_PRESENCE) {
4248 DPRINTF(("%s: headphone has been inserted.\n", __func__));
4249 generic_mixer_pinctrl(this, STAC9200_NID_SPEAKER, 0);
4250 } else {
4251 DPRINTF(("%s: headphone has been pulled out.\n", __func__));
4252 generic_mixer_pinctrl(this, STAC9200_NID_SPEAKER, CORB_PWC_OUTPUT);
4253 }
4254 break;
4255 default:
4256 printf("%s: unknown tag: %d\n", __func__, tag);
4257 }
4258 return 0;
4259}
